The paper discusses a new method for stopping active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The method is based on stabilizing predictions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the need for handling different annotation/performance tradeoff valuations, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
